The paper deals with the error probability of lattice codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Voronoi cells and moments suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on a specific type of lattice (root lattice $A_n$) suggests a possible connection to algebraic geometry (cs.AG) or representation theory (cs.RT).
